This script creates a docker image containing golang and rabbitmq server, exposing ports 15672 and 5672 and 8080 to the host machine's equivalent ports.
after starting the container by running this script, sending a JSON message to a specific app
can be done by sending the json object as the request body of an http request to the url "server_ip:8080/tag"
where tag is the name of the destination app.


The script can be run as follows:
-----------------------------------

** grant the script permissions
$ chmod 700 auto-build

** run the script
$ ./auto-build
